## Definition of Done (initial design shaping)

Consider the “initial shaping” complete when:
- A style + palette + motion profile + typography pack are chosen and documented
- Tokens are defined and used consistently (no random colors/spacing/animations)
- Core components have consistent states (hover/active/focus/disabled/error/loading)
- The design reads well in Vietnamese + English
- Motion respects `prefers-reduced-motion`
- The UI remains readable and performant (no blanket heavy blur/filters)

## Checklist (review gates)

Use this as a quick review before calling the UI “ready”:
- **Direction locked**: exactly 1 style + 1 palette + 1 motion profile chosen (or justified custom).
- **Tokens first**: colors/type/spacing/radius/motion tokens exist and are used (no one-off magic values unless justified).
- **Bilingual safety**: Vietnamese diacritics render cleanly; long Vietnamese strings wrap gracefully; mixed EN+VI looks natural.
- **A11y basics**: keyboard navigation works; focus states are visible; primary text contrast is sufficient; `prefers-reduced-motion` is respected.
- **States covered**: hover/active/focus/disabled/error/loading/empty exist for core components.
- **Motion discipline**: one “hero moment” max for `MO-SUBTLE`; avoid constant scroll-jank; keep effects purposeful.
- **Performance sanity**: avoid blanket heavy blur/filters; prefer transform/opacity for animations; keep decorative layers controlled.
- **Consistency**: components share the same radii, shadows, borders, and spacing rhythm; no visual drift between screens.